Class PropertyDefinitionCache

java.lang.Object
  com.cboe.domain.property.PropertyDefinitionCache

public class PropertyDefinitionCache
extends java.lang.Object

Cache for the property definitions. This class is a singleton. Nothing is ever removed from the cache.

public void acceptPropertyUpdate(com.cboe.interfaces.domain.property.PropertyServicePropertyGroup group)

acceptPropertyRemove

public void acceptPropertyRemove(java.lang.String category,
                                 java.lang.String key)
Accept events for a property being removed. This means that a set of category definitions has been totally removed. This is bizare, but go ahead and remove them from the cache.

Parameters:
category - The category the group was in.
key - The key for the group that was removed.
